caption: Great hidden gem in Hollywood! Dark, dim, quaint ambience, with great weekday specials on both drinks and food. The Monday grilled cheese sandwiches they offer are delicious! The Brie cheese, sautéed apple & apricot butter grilled cheese was finger licking good!
My friends and I frequent this place. Drinks are well made, good crowd and sometimes fun DJs.

I'm so happy Perch was open during pandemic. They did a great job with spacing out tables for social distancing. The  service is always great. The manager was even checking on us. The food and drinks always on point. Amazing  views. Will definitely come back.
Good experience here. Met many good friends and they had good music. They also had tacos outside where you can just chill outside and dance/hangout. Cool setting!

Sunday brunch - great menu. Swordfish BLT was awesome, probably one of the best BLT I've had. The Doris ordered strawberry pancakes which were a little bit disappointing, not fluffy and pretty moist/oily inside. Service was so so, seemed like they didn't have enough kitchen staff.

We had half an hour to kill before The Book of Mormon at the Pantages so I said, hey let's check out the historic Frolic Room!  Honestly I expected more than the most generic of dive bars.  Aside from the mural of Old Hollywood caricatures on the back wall, once inside I really could have been at any old dive in the FL.
